body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
See diff of t_lint_width.v below

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
master

What OS and distribution are you using? 
Windows WSL Ubuntu

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?
Sure

```
~/verilator/test_regress$ git diff t/t_lint_width.v
diff --git a/test_regress/t/t_lint_width.v b/test_regress/t/t_lint_width.v
index 18db807d8..ee672cb87 100644
--- a/test_regress/t/t_lint_width.v
+++ b/test_regress/t/t_lint_width.v
@@ -12,6 +12,12 @@ module t ();
    wire [4:0] suma = five + 1'b1;
    wire [4:0] sumb = 1'b1 + five;
    wire [4:0] sumc = five - 1'b1;
+   wire [4:0] sumd = -five;
+//   wire [5:0] sume = -five; //should pass: -(-16) == 16
+   wire [5:0] sumf = suma + five;
+//   wire [6:0] sumg = suma + five; //bad
+   wire [5:0] sumh = suma + sumb + five; //should fail? Either extend all the way or always wrap two's complement?
+   wire [6:0] sumh = suma + sumb + five;

    // Relatively harmless < or <= compared with something less wide
    localparam [1:0] THREE = 3;
```
